                            <comment id="15927658" author="pvillard" created="Thu, 16 Mar 2017 08:23:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=uwegeercken&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;uwegeercken&quot;&gt;uwegeercken&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you give more details? What is the configuration of your processor? What is the arborescence you are watching? What are the existing files when the processor is started, what are the new files added?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking for a way to reproduce what you are experiencing.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15929004" author="uwegeercken" created="Thu, 16 Mar 2017 22:08:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for being short worded...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I create small and simple json files from shell scripts in a central folder. They are used for monitoring some processes. They contain just a few bytes of data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have configured the processor for multiple files, given a reg expression (monitoring_.*.json), and provided the base directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I start the processor and there are a few json files in the folder and the TailFile picks them up correctly. But then over time more json files are created. These new files don&apos;t get picked up unless I stop and start the TailFile processor. But when I do, they get correctly picked up.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15932523" author="pvillard" created="Mon, 20 Mar 2017 11:36:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=uwegeercken&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;uwegeercken&quot;&gt;uwegeercken&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I looked into it a bit and here are some remarks:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;at the moment, to have the expected behavior the rolling strategy must be set to &quot;changing name&quot; to have the lookup frequency being used. I&apos;ll submit a PR to fix it. Can you check if this solves your problem?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;just as a reminder (not related to the issue), the TailFile processor expects a carriage return at the end of the line to process the line. I don&apos;t know how are your JSON formatted but just in case...&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
